gantt
Section Prepare Vegetables
Dice 1 large fresh fennel bulb into .25 inch cubes, add to a medium bowl :a, 2017-01-01, 3d
Dice 1 medium onion into .25 inch cubes, add to fennel mixture :b, after a, 3d
Coursely grind .5 TSP anise seeds and add to fennel mixture :c, after b, 3d
Add 1 TSP salt and 1 tsp pepper to fennel mixture :d, after c, 1d
Section Cook Couscous 
Melt 1.5 TBSP butter in large saucepan over medium heat :e, after d, 5d
Add fennel mixture and saute until fennel is almost tender :f, after e, 10d
Add 2 cups of low-sodium chicken stock and 1 cup of water to pot and bring to boil :g, after f, 5d
Stir in couscous and remove from heat.  Let stand, covered until liquid is absorbed :crit, h, after g, 10d
Toast pine nuts in a dry skillet over medium heat, being careful not to burn them :i, after g, 5d
Fluff couscous with fork, stir in pine nuts and adjust seasoning to taste :j, after i, 1d
&&&
Ingredients
1 1/2 tablespoons butter
1 large fresh fennel bulb, cut into 1/4-inch cubes (about 2 cups)
1 medium onion cut into 1/4-inch cubes
1/2 teaspoon fennel or anise seeds, coarsely ground in mortar with
pestle or in spice mill (optional)
2 cups low-salt chicken broth
1 cup water
2 cups couscous (about 12 ounces)
1/4 cup pine nuts, toasted
3 tablespoons chopped fresh chives or scallions
